==English==
===Etymology===
The etymology is the subject of speculation, with hypotheses ranging from derivation from a combination of [[glom]] and [[jump]] to an acronym of "Grab, Latch On, Maintain Pressure".  No authoritative etymology exists, however.
===Transitive verb===
[[Category:English transitive verbs]]
[[Category:English slang]]
{{en-verb|glomp}}
# (''slang'') to embrace enthusiastically; to pounce on and hug, often from a running start. Generally feminine or childish in nature.
#*2000:"Nope. Every instance he's near her he tries to '''glomp''' her. If she shows affection to Ranma, he attacks Ranma. " &mdash; [http://groups.google.com./group/rec.arts.anime.fandom/msg/f1d35cbb99146224 KATHYNEW]
